<br>
<br>
Due to the fact that there are a lot of common issues to Albion and Hibernia's Light Tanks, I am combining both reports into one, so I don't have to repeat myself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Charge:<br>
<br>
This is a great ability so far in RvR. However, it needs to have it's speed upgraded slightly to something faster than merely an endurance-free sprint. Also, it is currently switching to sprint at the end of its duration, and starts to eat up endurance. There is no animation/effect for charge currently.<br>
<br>
Flurry:<br>
<br>
This ability is working well to compensate for our lack of front-load ramage in RvR. It is also lacking an effect. <br>
<br>
Styles:<br>
<br>
Styles are the #1 complaint for Blademasters and Mercenaries. Rudely put, our style lines suck. As stated previously on the TL boards, we have snare styles which are completely useless due to the fact that our offhand weapon will immediately break the snare.<br>
<br>
Blademasters have no medium duration stun style in their line. I ask that the level 34 style -- Meteor Shower, be changed to at least a medium duration stun. This makes the chain more useful, and comparable to the level 44 Mercenary style, Hypnotic Darkness.<br>
<br>
The level 10 Celtic Dual Style, Gale, should be changed to an anytime detaunt, and the level 15 style, Thunderstorm, should take the bleed damage from Gale.<br>
<br>
Mercenaries have no anytime chain in the Dual Wield line. Taking the level 21 style, Penumbra, and having it chain off of the level 15 style, Misty Gloom, would help to even this out.<br>
<br>
Several of our styles have heavy bleed damage.... which doesn't really add that much in the way of damage. Doubing the amount of bleed damage on heavy duration bleeds would actually make the level 50 Mercenary style something to fear, as well as making the level 44 Blademaster style (the third in a chain) something worthwhile to pull off.<br>
<br>
Mercenary-specific issues:<br>
<br>
Please make Dirty Tricks/Increased fumbles either unresistable, or drop the timer down to 10 minutes. Having an ability that only works every half an hour and gets resisted is silly.<br>
<br>
<br>
Equipment Issues:<br>
<br>
Is there any way to make a shield equippable in the 2H slot? This would enable Mercenaries and Blademasters to be able to hot-key a shield for engage. At this moment in time, a lot of backpack juggling has to occur before we can accomplish this.<br>
<br>
There are new off-hand thrusters, and a new off-hand blunt in Hibernia, but they have not made it to live yet. Preminary feedback from Pendragon has been positive. Will cover this more in the next report.<br>
<br>
A small, rabid portion of the Mercenary community slipped me a bribe, and asked that I ask the items developers to put more axe drops out there. There are currently only 2 high-end axe drops in Albion, adding one or two more would be very profitable to the Guild of Shadows.<br>
<br>
<br>
Realm Abilities: <br>
<br>
Everyone is very happy with the reduced costs. This helps us out a lot in RvR, and was a great change.<br>
<br>
Prevent Flight -- if this were lowered to cost 10 points, it is likely that more Light Tanks would purchase it. That's a lot of RSPS to shell out for a 35% chance to snare.<br>
<br>
Winter Moon and Void have basically been superceded by Flurry. I don't know of a single Blademaster or Mercenary that has these realm abilities. Please scrap them and give us something else. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all, things are looking up for both Hibernia's and Albion's light tank classes. We are finally starting to live up to our names. Some adjustments to our styles should help, and hopefully, we don't need any more &quot;pushbutton&quot; fixes.... we're running out of room on our hotbars.<br>
<br>
